# Documentation Rules

These rules apply when writing documentation or comments.

## JSDoc Comments

Always include JSDoc comments for exported functions with parameter types and return types:

```typescript
/**
 * Processes user input and returns formatted result
 * @param input - The raw user input string
 * @param options - Processing options
 * @returns The processed and formatted result
 * @throws {ValidationError} When input validation fails
 */
export const processUserInput = (
  input: string,
  options: ProcessingOptions
): Promise<string> => {
  // implementation
};
```

## Inline Comments

Use inline comments sparingly and only for complex business logic:

```typescript
// Calculate compound interest using formula: A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt)
const compoundInterest = (principal: number, rate: number, time: number): number => {
  return principal * Math.pow(1 + rate / 12, 12 * time);
};
```
